INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES (1,'Prototypes','prototypes','','<p><a href=\"../joomla/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;layout=blog&amp;id=1&amp;Itemid=3\">Prototypes</a></p>\r\n<p>Very brief description of prototypes (1 to 2 sentences) should go here.</p>\r\n<p>Recent prototypes:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Prototype Title 1</li>\r\n<li>PT Title 2</li>\r\n<li>Prototype Title 3</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">More...</p>','',-2,1,0,11,'2010-11-30 19:16:45',62,'','2010-12-10 20:15:43',62,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-11-30 19:16:45','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','show_title=0\nlink_titles=0\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=0\nshow_create_date=0\nshow_modify_date=0\nshow_pdf_icon=0\nshow_print_icon=0\nshow_email_icon=0\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=',8,0,0,'','',0,3,'robots=\nauthor='),(2,'Structured Evaluations','structured-evaluations-article','','<p><a href=\"../joomla/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;layout=blog&amp;id=2&amp;Itemid=4\">Structured Evaluations</a></p>\r\n<p>Very brief description of structured evaluations should go here.</p>\r\n<p>Recent structured evaluations:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open Source Data Mining Tools</li>\r\n<li>Structured Eval 2</li>\r\n<li>Structured Eval 3</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>More...</p>\r\n<p> </p>','',-2,1,0,11,'2010-11-30 19:33:49',62,'','2010-12-10 20:15:26',62,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-11-30 19:33:49','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','show_title=0\nlink_titles=0\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=0\nshow_create_date=0\nshow_modify_date=0\nshow_pdf_icon=0\nshow_print_icon=0\nshow_email_icon=0\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=',8,0,0,'','',0,1,'robots=\nauthor='),(3,'Brief Reviews ','brief-reviews-article','','<p><a href=\"../joomla/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;layout=blog&amp;id=3&amp;Itemid=5\">Brief Reviews</a></p>\r\n<p>Very short description of brief reviews should go here.</p>\r\n<p>Recent brief reviews:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>GeoDa and OpenGeoDa</li>\r\n<li>Brief review 2</li>\r\n<li>Brief review 3</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>','',-2,1,0,11,'2010-11-30 19:34:22',62,'','2010-12-10 20:15:14',62,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-11-30 19:34:22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','show_title=0\nlink_titles=0\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=0\nshow_create_date=0\nshow_modify_date=0\nshow_pdf_icon=0\nshow_print_icon=0\nshow_email_icon=0\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=',10,0,0,'','',0,3,'robots=\nauthor='),(4,'  Strategic Health IT Advanced Research Projects (SHARP) Program  ','news-article','','<p class=\"icon\"><img src=\"images/stories/sharp_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Office of the National Coordinator for Health Information Technology logo\" title=\"Office of the National Coordinator for Health Information Technology logo\" align=\"left\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"art_title\"><a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=4:news-article&amp;catid=4:news&amp;Itemid=6\"> Strategic Health IT Advanced Research Projects (SHARP) Program</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"tag\">$60 Million Awarded for the SHARP Program</p>\r\n<p>The Office of the National Coordinator for Health Information Technology  (ONC) has awarded $60 million in cooperative agreements for the Strategic Health IT Advanced Research Projects (SHARP) Program. The SHARP program seeks to support improvements in the quality, safety, and  efficiency of healthcare, through advanced information  technology. The research projects supported by the SHARP program will focus on solving  current and expected future challenges that represent barriers to adoption and  meaningful use of health IT. These projects will focus on areas where \"breakthrough\" advances are needed to realize the full potential of health  IT.</p>\r\n','\r\n<p><br />Each awardee in the SHARP Program will implement a focused research project in one of the following four areas where breakthrough advances are needed to address barriers to the adoption of health IT to meet the goal of making electronic health records (EHRs) available for all Americans by 2014.</p>\r\n<ol class=\"sum33\">\r\n<li class=\"sum2\">Security of Health Information Technology: This research area addresses the challenges of developing security and risk mitigation policies and the technologies necessary to build and preserve the public trust as health IT systems become ubiquitous. <br /><em>Awardee: University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign (#10510624) </em></li>\r\n<br />\r\n<li class=\"sum2\">Patient-Centered Cognitive Support: This research area addresses the challenge of harnessing the power of health IT to integrate with, enhance, and support clinicians‚Äô reasoning and decision-making, rather than forcing them into a mode of thinking that is natural to machines but not to people. <br /><em>Awardee: The University of Texas Health Science Center at Houston (#10510592)</em></li>\r\n<br />\r\n<li class=\"sum2\">Healthcare Application and Network Platform Architectures: This research area focuses on the development of new and improved architectures that are necessary to achieve electronic exchange and use of health information in a secure, private, and accurate manner. <br /><em>Awardee: Harvard University (#10510924)</em></li>\r\n<br />\r\n<li class=\"sum2\">Secondary Use of EHR Data: This research area focuses on strategies to make use of data that will be stored in EHRs for improving the overall quality of health care, while maintaining privacy and security of the data. <br /><em>Awardee: Mayo Clinic College of Medicine (#10510949)</em></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><br /><br />Projects will be guided by a two-part mission:</p>\r\n<ol class=\"sum33\">\r\n<li class=\"sum2\">Implementing a collaborative, interdisciplinary program of research addressing short- and long-term challenges in their respective focus area;</li>\r\n<br />\r\n<li class=\"sum2\">Developing and implementing a cooperative program between health IT stakeholders, researchers, industry, health care providers, and others, to transition the research findings into practice.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><br />All results of research will be transitioned into practice as soon as possible. Projects will develop technology solutions in their selected area of research and make information solutions available to the health IT market, in addition to making research results available through publication.</p>\r\n<p><br />Each cooperative agreement has a four-year project period. Progress of each project will be evaluated regularly. Additional information is available at <a class=\"reg\" href=\"http://HealthIT.HHS.Gov/Programs/SHARP\" target=\"_blank\">http://HealthIT.HHS.Gov/Programs/SHARP</a></p>\r\n<p> </p>',1,2,0,4,'2010-11-30 20:39:38',62,'','2011-05-10 14:56:51',62,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-11-30 20:39:38','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','show_title=0\nlink_titles=0\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=0\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=0\nshow_pdf_icon=0\nshow_print_icon=0\nshow_email_icon=0\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=',31,0,7,'','',0,130,'robots=\nauthor='),(5,'  ATSDR ToxGuide for the iOS Platform  ','-atsdr-toxguide-for-the-ios-platform-','','<p class=\"icon\"><img src=\"images/stories/atsdr_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"ATSDR icon\" title=\"ATSDR icon\" align=\"left\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"art_title\"><a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=5:-atsdr-toxguide-for-the-ios-platform-&amp;catid=1:prototypes&amp;Itemid=3\">ATSDR ToxGuide for the iOS Platform</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"info\"><strong>Project Type: </strong>Prototype | <strong>Start Date:</strong> 7/15/2010 | <strong>Platform:</strong> iOS | <strong>Version:</strong> 1.0</p>\r\n<p class=\"tag\">Toxic Substance Quick Reference Guides for the iPhone</p>\r\n<p>The ATSDR ToxGuides<sup>TM</sup> are quick reference guides providing information such as chemical and physical properties, sources of exposure, routes of exposure, minimal risk levels, children\'s health, and health effects. The ToxGuides also discuss how the substance might interact in the environment. The ToxGuides were developed by the ATSDR Division of Toxicology and Environmental Medicine. Information is excerpted from the corresponding toxicological profiles.</p>\r\n','\r\n<p><br />Currently ToxGuides are available in both the standard HTML or PDF format, and can be found at: <a class=\"reg\" href=\"http://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/toxguides/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/toxguides/index.asp</a>. This project examined the preliminary design and layout of a prototype ToxGuide as an app for the Apple iPhone.</p>\r\n<p class=\"sum2\"><img src=\"images/brief_reviews/screenshot_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"screenshots icon\" title=\"screenshots icon\" align=\"middle\" /> Screenshots <span style=\"font-size:10px; color:#777575; padding-left:3px;\">(view screenshots by clicking the thumbnails below)</span> <br /><br /><img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"5\" height=\"1\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/ATSDR_1screen.png\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/ATSDR_1thumb.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\" title=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\" /></a> <img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"12\" height=\"1\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/ATSDR_2screen.png\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/ATSDR_2thumb.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\" title=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\" /></a><img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"12\" height=\"1\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/ATSDR_3screen.png\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/ATSDR_3thumb.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\" title=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\" /></a></p>\r\n<ul class=\"sum2\">\r\n<img src=\"images/stories/project_resources.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Resources icon\" title=\"Resources icon\" align=\"absMiddle\" /> Resources\r\n<li class=\"sum3\"><a class=\"reg\" href=\"http://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/toxguides/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">ToxGuides on CDC.gov</a></li>\r\n</ul>',1,1,0,1,'2010-07-06 01:19:00',62,'','2011-12-01 17:20:16',62,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-12-08 14:19:04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','show_title=0\nlink_titles=0\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=0\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=0\nshow_pdf_icon=0\nshow_print_icon=0\nshow_email_icon=0\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=',40,0,8,'','',0,174,'robots=\nauthor='),(6,'WISQARS Database Reporting for the iOS Platform','wisqars-database-reporting-for-the-ios-platform','','<p class=\"icon\"><img src=\"images/stories/wisquars_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"WISQARS icon\" title=\"WISQARS icon\" align=\"left\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"art_title\"><a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=6:wisqars-database-reporting-for-the-ios-platform&amp;catid=1:prototypes&amp;Itemid=3\"> WISQARS Database Reporting for the iOS Platform</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"info\"><strong>Project Type: </strong>Prototype | <strong>Start Date:</strong> 7/29/2010 | <strong>Platform:</strong> iOS | <strong>Version:</strong> 1.0</p>\r\n<p class=\"tag\">Easy to understand, catchy tagline</p>\r\n<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliqu