s a reference for doctors and related parties on the identification of and treatment regimen for STDs.</p>\r\n','\r\n<p><br />These guidelines for the treatment of persons who have or are at risk for sexually transmitted diseases (STDs) were updated by CDC after consultation with a group of professionals knowledgeable in the field of STDs who met in Atlanta on April 18–30, 2009. The information in this report updates the 2006 Guidelines for Treatment of Sexually Transmitted Diseases (MMWR 2006;55[No. RR–11]).</p>\r\n<p class=\"sum2\"><img src=\"images/brief_reviews/screenshot_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"screenshots icon\" title=\"screenshots icon\" align=\"middle\" /> Screenshots <span style=\"font-size:10px; color:#777575; padding-left:3px;\"> (view screenshots by clicking the thumbnails below)</span> <br /><br /> <img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"12px\" height=\"1px\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/std1.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #1\"> <img src=\"images/prototypes/std1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"STDApp Screenshot #1\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #1\" width=\"60\" height=\"91/\" /></a> <img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"12px\" height=\"1px\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/std2.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #2\"> <img src=\"images/prototypes/std2.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"STDApp Screenshot #2\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #2\" width=\"60\" height=\"91/\" /></a> <img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"12px\" height=\"1px\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/std3.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #3\"> <img src=\"images/prototypes/std3.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"STDApp Screenshot #3\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #3\" width=\"60\" height=\"91/\" /></a> <img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"12px\" height=\"1px\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/std4.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #4\"> <img src=\"images/prototypes/std4.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"STDApp Screenshot #4\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #4\" width=\"60\" height=\"91/\" /></a> <img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"12px\" height=\"1px\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/std5.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #5\"> <img src=\"images/prototypes/std5.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"STDApp Screenshot #5\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #5\" width=\"60\" height=\"91/\" /></a> <img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"12px\" height=\"1px\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/std6.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #6\"> <img src=\"images/prototypes/std6.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"STDApp Screenshot #6\" title=\"STDApp Screenshot #6\" width=\"60\" height=\"91/\" /></a></p>',1,1,0,1,'2010-12-08 14:19:04',62,'','2011-05-24 15:25:40',62,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-12-08 14:19:04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','show_title=0\nlink_titles=0\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=0\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=0\nshow_pdf_icon=0\nshow_print_icon=0\nshow_email_icon=0\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=',6,0,11,'','',0,71,'robots=\nauthor='),(70,'Public Health News','ph-news','','<p class=\"icon\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/health_news_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"PHNews icon\" title=\"PHNews icon\" align=\"left\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"art_title\"><a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=70:-ph-news-&amp;catid=1:prototypes&amp;Itemid=3\">Public Health News</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"info\"><strong>Project Type: </strong>Prototype | <strong>Start Date:</strong> 11/15/2010 | <strong>Platform:</strong> Web | <strong>Version:</strong> 1.0</p>\r\n<p class=\"tag\">Treemap Representation of Public Health Related News</p>\r\n<p>Inspired by <a class=\"reg\" href=\"http://newsmap.jp\">http://newsmap.jp</a>, this app uses the Google News API to visualize public health related news according to relevance.</p>\r\n','\r\n<p><br />This tool extracts data from Google News and leverages the \"Treemap\" algorithm to view the information in a very efficient way:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"sum3\">\r\n<li class=\"sum2\">The larger the rectangle and font size the more popular the article topic.</li>\r\n<li class=\"sum2\">The brighter the background color, the more recent the news article.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br />This \"Public Health News\" prototype has the potential to improve the timeliness of decision making by federal, state and local public health programs by augmenting their ability to rapidly gather and filter relevant public health news. Unlike the existing Newsmap tool, this prototype does not require flash, and, once optimized, can be used on handheld devices (e.g., iPad &amp; iPhone) which do not support flash. In addition, this prototype allows for extensive customization- to meet the specific need of the public health user.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>Source code</strong>: <a class=\"reg\" href=\"http://code.google.com/p/informaticslab/source/browse/#svn/HealthNews\">http://code.google.com/p/informaticslab/source/browse/#svn/HealthNews</a></p>\r\n<!--\r\n<p><b>Launch Application</b>: <a class=\"reg\" href=\"http://bit.ly/phhealthnews\" mce_href=\"http://bit.ly/phhealthnews\">http://bit.ly/phhealthnews</a></p>\r\n-->\r\n<p class=\"sum2\"><img src=\"images/brief_reviews/screenshot_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"screenshots icon\" title=\"screenshots icon\" align=\"middle\" /> Screenshots <span style=\"font-size:10px; color:#777575; padding-left:3px;\">(view screenshots by clicking the thumbnails below)</span> <br /><br /><img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"5\" height=\"1\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/phhealthnews1.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"PHNews Screenshot\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/phhealthnews1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"PHNews Screenshot\" title=\"PHNews Screenshot\" width=\"200\" height=\"100\" /></a></p>',1,1,0,1,'2010-12-09 19:02:00',62,'','2012-03-09 16:16:24',62,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-12-09 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','show_title=0\nlink_titles=0\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=0\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=0\nshow_pdf_icon=0\nshow_print_icon=0\nshow_email_icon=0\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=',22,0,10,'','',0,75,'robots=\nauthor='),(71,'SAMWise+','samwise-plus','','<p class=\"icon\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/samwise_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"SAMWise+ icon\" title=\"SAMWise+ icon\" align=\"left\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"art_title\"><a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=71:-samwise-plus;catid=1:prototypes&amp;Itemid=3\">SAMWise+</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"info\"><strong>Project Type: </strong>Prototype | <strong>Start Date:</strong> 2/05/2010 | <strong>Platform:</strong> Web | <strong>Version:</strong> 1.0</p>\r\n<p class=\"tag\">Health Literacy Index Web Tool</p>\r\n<p>The goal of this prototype has been to work with subject matter experts to ultimately create a digital version of a Health Literacy Index (HLI). As an intermediate step to creating an HLI, a digital tool, Samwise+, has been created based on the Suitiablity Assessment of Materials (SAM) tool. SAMWise+ has the potential to be an important step forward, has it encourages individuals to use a scoring tool, other than readability formulas. One other core goal is to scan existing literature to identify which of the SAM criteria can be automated/digitized and if so, the level of effort necessary to automate the scoring.</p>\r\n','\r\n<p><br /><strong>Source code</strong>: <a class=\"reg\" href=\"http://code.google.com/p/informaticslab/source/browse/#svn/Samwise\">http://code.google.com/p/informaticslab/source/browse/#svn/Samwise</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Launch Application</strong>: <a class=\"reg\" href=\"http://207.138.115.204/Samwise/\">http://207.138.115.204/Samwise/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"sum2\"><img src=\"images/brief_reviews/screenshot_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"screenshots icon\" title=\"screenshots icon\" align=\"middle\" /> Screenshots <span style=\"font-size:10px; color:#777575; padding-left:3px;\">(view screenshots by clicking the thumbnails below)</span> <br /><br /><img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"5\" height=\"1\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/samwise1.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"SAMwise+ Screenshot\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/samwise1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"SAMwise+ Screenshot\" title=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\" width=\"120\" height=\"100\" /></a> <img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"5\" height=\"1\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/samwise2.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"SAMwise+ Screenshot\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/samwise2.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"SAMwise+ Screenshot\" title=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\" width=\"120\" height=\"100\" /></a> <img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"5\" height=\"1\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/samwise3.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"SAMwise+ Screenshot\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/samwise3.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"SAMwise+ Screenshot\" title=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\" width=\"120\" height=\"100\" /></a> <img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"5\" height=\"1\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/samwise4.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"SAMwise+ Screenshot\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/samwise4.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"SAMwise+ Screenshot\" title=\"ATSDR ToxGuide Screenshot\" width=\"120\" height=\"100\" /></a></p>',1,1,0,1,'2011-01-02 22:10:00',62,'','2011-12-01 17:19:23',62,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2011-01-02 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','show_title=0\nlink_titles=0\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=0\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=0\nshow_pdf_icon=0\nshow_print_icon=0\nshow_email_icon=0\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=',9,0,9,'','',0,61,'robots=\nauthor='),(72,'2011 iFund Challenge funding recipient','ifund-challenge','','<p class=\"icon\"><img src=\"images/news/ifund_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"iFund Challenge logo\" title=\"iFund Challenge logo\" align=\"left\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"art_title\"><span style=\"position: relative; top: 10px;\"><a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=72:ifund-challenge&amp;catid=4:news&amp;Itemid=6\">2011 iFund Challenge Funding Recipient</a></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p class=\"tag\">IRDU collaborates with Laboratory Science Policy Practice Program Office (LSPPPO) and is selected to receive funding through CDC\'s 2011 iFund Challenge.</p>\r\n<p>The Informatics Research &amp; Development Unit (IRDU) was competitively selected, in collaboration with LSPPPO, to receive financial support from the Innovation Fund Challenge to develop smartphone/smartpad applications to improve clinical decision support related to abnormal laboratory test results (e.g., a prolonged partial thromoboplastin time).  Out of 140 submitted proposals, only 11 projects were awarded funding.</p>\r\n<p> </p>','',1,2,0,4,'2011-05-23 14:11:00',62,'TGS','2011-05-23 20:55:42',62,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2011-05-23 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','show_title=0\nlink_titles=0\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=0\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=0\nshow_pdf_icon=0\nshow_print_icon=0\nshow_email_icon=0\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=',14,0,5,'','',0,29,'robots=\nauthor='),(74,'Prolonged PTT Advisor for the iOS Platform','prolonged-ptt-advisor-for-iphone','','<p class=\"icon\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/ptt_advisor_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"PTT Advisor icon\" title=\"PTT Advisor icon\" align=\"left\" style=\"float: left; border: 0;\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"art_title\"><a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=74:-prolonged-ptt-advisor-for-iphone-&amp;catid=1:prototypes&amp;Itemid=3\">Prolonged PTT Advisor for the iOS Platform</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"info\"><strong>Project Type: </strong>Prototype | <strong>Start Date:</strong> 4/1/2011 | <strong>Platform:</strong> iOS | <strong>Version:</strong> 1.0</p>\r\n<p class=\"tag\">Prolonged PTT Advisor for the iPhone</p>\r\n<p>The prototype is a smartphone application (for the iOS platform) to assist clinical providers with management of patients requiring complex coagulation testing, which when misused can result in adverse patient outcomes. The application leverages five coagulation testing algorithms.</p>\r\n','\r\n<p><br />These five algorithms were developed by a group of volunteer laboratory experts working together on a CDC-sponsored team as part of the Clinical Laboratory Integration into Healthcare Collaborative (CLIHC)™ project. The prototype leverages the algorithms as documented in flow charts and turns them into electronic, interactive, decision support tools for clinical provider use. The algorithms will be organized digitally to allow the user to easily walk through a complicated flow diagram by answering one question at a time in an interactive format. The prototype will also include the ability to obtain real-time information about the effectiveness and use of the application.</p>\r\n<p class=\"sum2\"><img src=\"images/brief_reviews/screenshot_icon.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"screenshots icon\" title=\"screenshots icon\" align=\"middle\" /> Screenshots <span style=\"font-size:10px; color:#777575; padding-left:3px;\">(view screenshots by clicking the thumbnails below)</span> <br /><br /><img src=\"images/stories/pixel_shim.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"spacer\" width=\"5\" height=\"1\" /> <a href=\"images/prototypes/ptt1.png\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"PTT Screenshot #1\"><img src=\"images/prototypes/ptt1.png\" border